The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Geneva, Nov. 27: Ministers from the WTOs most influential powers, including India, will meet early next year to make their first joint attempt at reviving global trade talks since their collapse last summer. Top representatives of the United States, the European Union, Japan, Australia, India and Brazil are among those expected to gather on the sidelines at the world economic forums annual four-day meeting of global leaders in Davos, Switzerland.

 Calcutta, Nov. 27: McLeod Russel India will put up the proposal of amalgamation of its wholly owned subsidiary, Doom Dooma Tea, at its board meeting on December 1.

 New Delhi, Nov. 27: The government is likely to notify the FDI limit in stock exchanges within a week, a senior finance ministry official said today. Sebi had earlier come out with guidelines for ownership in stock exchanges, under which 49 per cent stake would be held by members brokers and a single investor was allowed to pick a maximum 5 per cent. 

 Chennai, Nov. 27: The government will soon announce a policy on spectrum allocation for launching third generation (3G) services in mobile telephony, IT minister Dayanidhi Maran said today.

 Mumbai, Nov. 27: Pantaloon Retail has got shareholders approval for a stock split in the ratio of 1:5. The shareholders approved the subdivision of shares of Rs 10 each to five of Rs 2.




